{
  "texts": [
    "A unified framework for LLM-based unit test generation, adopting a systems engineering view.",
    "It distinguishes the core prompt-driven generation workflow from a foundational model preparation stage and enhancement pipelines for context enrichment and quality assurance.",
    "This framework serves as the structural basis for the analysis in this survey.Surrounding this core are techniques designed to specialize the model and refine its inputs and outputs.",
    "Model preparation operates prior to deployment, involving techniques such as pre-training [5,115] or fine-tuning [110,124,126] to specialize the LLM for code synthesis tasks.",
    "Moving to the inference stage, contextual enrichment addresses the \"semantic gap\" by employing static and dynamic analysis to construct a context-rich prompt, thereby preventing compilation errors [118,150].Once the raw test code is produced, quality assurance loop mechanisms are triggered."
  ]
}